RAM	8 GB	16 GB or more
CPU	Dual-core processor	Quad-core or better
GPU	Not required for basic models	Required (e.g., NVIDIA CUDA-enabled)
Storage	10+ GB (for datasets & models)	SSD with 50+ GB free space

2. Software Requirements
Programming Language
Python 3.7 or higher

Libraries and Frameworks
Data Collection & Processing:

pandas, numpy, yfinance, pandas_datareader

Visualization:

matplotlib, seaborn, plotly

Statistical Modeling:

statsmodels, pmdarima

Machine Learning & Deep Learning:

scikit-learn, xgboost

tensorflow or keras (for LSTM/GRU)

Deployment:

Flask or Streamlit for web interface

gunicorn, Docker (optional, for production deployment)

3. Dataset Requirements
Historical Stock Market Data (daily or intraday)

Fields: Date, Open, High, Low, Close, Volume

Source: Yahoo Finance, Alpha Vantage, Quandl

Format: CSV or directly from API

4. Tools & Platforms
Development Environment: Jupyter Notebook, VS Code, PyCharm

Version Control: Git & GitHub

Cloud/Deployment Platforms:

For hosting: Heroku, Render, AWS, or Streamlit Sharing

For storage (optional): Google Drive, AWS S3

Optional: Google Colab (for free GPU)

5. User Requirements
Basic understanding of financial markets

Familiarity with Python and machine learning concepts
